NUMBER 2308
NAME Undergound, Waterfall
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
CHANNEL 134
REGION 131
*DESCRIPTION_START
You find yourself on what appears to be a vast underground lake. Water pours 
from a hole in the ceiling as a waterfall. The water comes crashing down into 
the lake throwing huge quantities of mist and water into the air. The walls and
lakeshore are covered in minerals and crystals where the heat from the volcano 
have evaporated the water. Noise from the volcano makes it very difficult to 
hear anything else. An opening in the north wall leads out.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1062
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The water rolls and bubbles as steam rises from its surface.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You start to enter the water but pull back from the heat.
  ECHO OTHERS Yo see %N aproach the water and then pull back.
ENDIF
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=2307
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You see an opening to the north where part of the wall seems to have collapsed.
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  RANDOM nrrtemp 1 100 0
  IFVAR nrrtemp > 95
    ECHO PLAYER You find a fire opal among the crystals.
    NEWITEM -1 116 ADJ1=126 VAL1=10000
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You search the area but find nothing of interest.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;
NUMBER 2309
NAME Underground, Lava Flow
DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
CHANNEL 134
REGION 131
*DESCRIPTION_START
This air in this room seems to waver before your eyes from the intense heat 
and burns as you attempt to breath. A river of lava flows down a channel in
the center of this room.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 2304
;item 0 river
ITEM 0 1675
EXTEND 0 of lava
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  ECHO PLAYER The heat from the lava is intense. The river of lava appears to narrow near the center of this chamber.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  ECHO PLAYER You attempt to enter the river of lava, but are forced back but the intense heat.
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 0
  ECHO PLAYER You reach out to touch the lava, but are driven back by the heat.
ENDIF
IFVERB JUMP 0
  CLEARVERB
  RANDOM nrrtemp 1 100 0
  IFVAR nrrtemp > 90
    ECHO PLAYER You attempt to jump across the river but don't quite make it.
    ECHO OTHERS You see %N try to jump across the river and fall into it instead.
    EQUAL BODYPOINTS 0
    DAMAGEPLR BURN 50 You are severly burned.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR NRRTEMP < 91
    ECHO PLAYER You jump neatly across the lava.
    ECHO OTHERS You see %N jump across the river of lava.
    DAMAGEPLR BURN 20 You are singed as you jump across.
    MOVE 2310
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;
